The paper deals with separation results in computational complexity, which is a central topic in cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses the use of local hidden variables in quantum mechanics, which falls under cs.QI (Quantum Physics). The concept of rank is also used extensively in the paper, which is a common theme in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the log-rank conjecture, which is a well-known problem in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
